-- China May Start Carbon Trading Trials in Some Regions, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-05T10:16:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/china-may-start-carbon-trading-trials-in-some-regions-xinhua-reports.html
China will encourage some regions to
start trials on carbon trading and study the possibility of
imposing carbon tariffs, the official Xinhua News Agency  said .  The National Development and Reform Commission plans
to establish a team to guide the trials, Xinhua said, citing Sun
Cuihua, deputy chief of the climate change department at the
national planner.  -- Alfred Cang  in Shanghai. Editor:  Tan Hwee Ann   To contact Bloomberg News staff on this story:
